  { question: "How many batteries can I recycle at once?", answer: "There's no strict limit, but large quantities may require special handling. Contact recyclers in advance for bulk collections." },
  { question: "Do electronics stores recycle batteries?", answer: "Many Best Buy, Staples, and other electronics retailers have battery recycling programs. Some offer trade-in incentives." },
  { question: "Can schools and offices recycle batteries?", answer: "Yes, most battery recyclers offer collection services for educational and business facilities, often with volume discounts." },
  { question: "What's the best time to recycle batteries?", answer: "Year-round, but many people recycle during spring cleaning or electronic upgrade seasons. Some facilities have special collection events." },
  { question: "Can I recycle batteries from medical devices?", answer: "Yes, but medical batteries may have special handling requirements. Contact specialized medical waste recyclers for proper disposal." },
  { question: "How do I dispose of button cell batteries?", answer: "Button cells can be recycled at most battery collection points. They're small but contain significant amounts of heavy metals." },
  { question: "Can I recycle batteries from solar panels?", answer: "Solar batteries require specialized recycling due to their unique chemistry. Look for facilities certified to handle solar battery systems." },
  
  // Industry and Future Trends
  { question: "What's the future of battery recycling technology?", answer: "Emerging technologies include AI-powered sorting, robotic disassembly, direct recycling processes, and advanced material recovery techniques." },
  { question: "How will EV battery recycling change the industry?", answer: "Massive EV adoption will create unprecedented battery waste volumes, driving innovation in large-scale recycling and second-life battery applications." },
  { question: "Can recycled battery materials be used in new batteries?", answer: "Yes, recycled materials can be used in new battery production, creating a circular economy for battery materials." },
  { question: "How does battery recycling support renewable energy?", answer: "Recycling recovers materials for energy storage systems, supporting the growth of solar, wind, and grid storage technologies." },
  { question: "What's the role of AI in battery recycling?", answer: "AI helps with automated sorting of battery types, predictive maintenance of recycling equipment, and optimization of recovery processes." },
  { question: "How will battery recycling evolve in the next decade?", answer: "Expect increased automation, improved recovery rates, integration with battery manufacturing, and expansion of collection networks." },
  { question: "What challenges will battery recycling face?", answer: "Increasing battery complexity, handling diverse chemistries, managing large EV battery packs, and developing cost-effective processes for rare materials." },
  { question: "How can consumers support battery recycling?", answer: "Properly dispose of old batteries at designated facilities, support EPR programs, and choose products from companies with strong recycling commitments." },
  { question: "What's the most promising battery recycling innovation?", answer: "Direct recycling technology, which recovers battery components without breaking chemical bonds, shows great promise for efficiency and performance." },
  { question: "How does battery recycling contribute to sustainability?", answer: "It reduces environmental impact, conserves resources, decreases carbon emissions from mining, and supports the transition to clean energy technologies." }
